rooms.name: Forbidden Library
rooms.description: You step into the Forbidden Library and silence closes around you, vast shelves receding into shadow like the ribs of some sleeping leviathan. Sparse furnishings — a single oaken lectern, a stone slab, a couple of wrought-iron chairs — stand isolated beneath a faint glyph-glow, while the air tastes of bitter ink and something older that was never meant to be read.

rooms.name: Ancient Crypt
rooms.description: You step into the Ancient Crypt, a vast vaulted chamber where your breath fogs in the cold, stale air and distant drip of water marks time like a slow metronome. Sparse furnishings — a few stone benches, a lone iron brazier, and several moss-cracked sarcophagi set into shadowed alcoves — throw long, patient silhouettes across the flagstones as dust motes drift through a light that seems almost reluctant to touch the room.

rooms.name: Arcane Laboratory
rooms.description: You step into the Arcane Laboratory, a vaulted, echoing chamber where space is measured in drifting motes of light rather than furniture. A lone iron table and a handful of glass phials catch a cold, rune-lit glow while the air tastes of ozone and bitter roots, and a low, throbbing hum of dormant spells vibrates just beneath the flagstones.

rooms.name: Noble's Bedroom
rooms.description: You step into a vast, echoing chamber that once belonged to a noble, where a solitary four-poster bed, a battered oak chest, and a lone chaise are spread so sparsely they seem like the remnants of a stage set. The air tastes of stale perfume and damp stone, each footfall ringing thinly as dust motes drift through a single shuttered window and the room holds its memories with cool, indifferent silence.

rooms.name: Haunted Crypt
rooms.description: You push through ironbound doors into the Haunted Crypt, a vaulted chamber where cold, ancient air pools like ink in the hollows. The space is vast and sparsely furnished—one cracked sarcophagus, a leaning stone altar, a lone flickering brazier—and every footstep rings, stirring thin, resentful whispers from the shadows.
